14 of a temporary event services permit including:
15 1. Sanitation standards;
16 2. Criteria for events that qualify;
17 3. Application requirements and fees; and
18 4. Any other requirements necessary to protect the public health and
19 safety.
20 (b) The temporary event services permit shall be valid only for the specific dates
21 and locations requested.
22 (c) No person other than a Kentucky-licensed cosmetologist, esthetician, limited
23 stylist, or nail technician shall perform services at a temporary event services
24 location, and no licensee shall perform services other than those authorized by
25 his or her respective license pursuant to KRS 317A.020.
26 (d) The Kentucky-licensed cosmetologist, esthetician, limited stylist, or nail
27 technician holding a temporary event services permit shall be liable for any
